snippet.textDisplay:
I feel like the other option to deal with the condensation would be to heat the garage.  I honestly don't know if it is even possible with how you've built the structure right into the rock, but it would be pleasant if it could be done.  My gut says it would require an airgap of some sort: cinder blocks, low density bricks, or high PSI foam.  It's too late for that, and I don't know if it could be reasonably heated as constructed.

I also worry about the diameter of the drainage tube, but I grew up in one of the few places that gets more rain than England (and currently live in a spot that averages higher than England's overall average, but not the maximum).
